Reasoning: The paper deals with the complexity of computing layout parameters in directed graphs, specifically semi-complete digraphs. This falls under the area of graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions the Exponential Time Hypothesis, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, covered by the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses minimal obstructions for having small cutwidth, which is related to the area of graph theory known as graph minors, covered by the sub-category cs.GT (Graph Theory).
